<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Phase 4 W3 C4 iter 8 — entitlements for the macOS reference client.

  `com.apple.developer.aps-environment` is the load-bearing key here.
  Without it `application(_:didRegisterForRemoteNotifications…)` is never
  invoked, the device-token callback never fires, and the gateway's
  APNs adapter has nowhere to push to.

  `development` is correct for unsigned/dev builds. A shipping build
  via the Mac App Store flips this to `production`; we don't ship
  there from C4 (see design doc out-of-scope §"Mac App Store
  distribution"), so `development` is the only target value.

  `com.apple.security.network.client` is required by the App Sandbox
  to make outbound HTTPS calls to the gateway. It's the minimum sandbox
  entitlement for a chat client; we *don't* enable
  `network.server` because the dev-push socket is a Unix-domain
  socket the gateway opens, not a TCP server we run.

  Keychain access groups are intentionally absent — the default group
  (the bundle id) is what `AuthStore` writes under, and we don't need
  to share creds with sibling apps yet.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.developer.aps-environment</key>
	<string>development</string>
	<key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
